## Section 22: Animation & Motion Patterns

### 22.1 Animation Principles

**Philosophy**: Animations should be purposeful, not decorative. Every animation serves to:
1. Guide user attention
2. Provide feedback
3. Maintain context during transitions
4. Reduce perceived loading time

**Timing Standards**:
- **Micro-interactions**: 150-200ms (hover, focus)
- **Component transitions**: 300ms (modals, drawers)
- **Page transitions**: 400-600ms (route changes)
- **Loading states**: Infinite (until data arrives)

---

### 22.2 Framer Motion Patterns

#### Page Entrance Animation
```tsx
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';

const pageVariants = {
  initial: { opacity: 0, y: 20 },
  animate: { opacity: 1, y: 0 },
  exit: { opacity: 0, y: -20 },
};

const Page = ({ children }) => (
  <motion.div
    variants={pageVariants}
    initial="initial"
    animate="animate"
    exit="exit"
    transition={{ duration: 0.4, ease: 'easeOut' }}
  >
    {children}
  </motion.div>
);
```

#### Stagger Children Animation
```tsx
const containerVariants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0 },
  show: {
    opacity: 1,
    transition: {
      staggerChildren: 0.1,
    },
  },
};

const itemVariants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 20 },
  show: { opacity: 1, y: 0 },
};

<motion.div variants={containerVariants} initial="hidden" animate="show">
  {items.map((item) => (
    <motion.div key={item.id} variants={itemVariants}>
      {item.content}
    </motion.div>
  ))}
</motion.div>
```

#### Success Animation Pattern
